                                                                                                                                Buttons

                                                                                                                                Sliding button

                                                                                                                                Stable

                                                                                                                                Sliding buttons are a variation of our known and loved primary rectangular buttons. Leveraging a different gesture to confirm an action, they help reduce accidental actions and reinforce intent.

                                                                                                                                Usage
                                                                                                                                Content
                                                                                                                                Specs
                                                                                                                                Status & changelog
                                                                                                                                Common alternative names
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Swipe button, draggable button


                                                                                                                                ﻿Questions, comments, feedback?

                                                                                                                                Leave a comment in Figma or reach out to us on Slack.

                                                                                                                                #base-design-support


                                                                                                                                Anatomy

                                                                                                                                A sliding button includes a button with a predefined icon and a base with a customizable label. All of the elements below are required.

                                                                                                                                Iconography

                                                                                                                                Sliding buttons leverage a single arrow icon to convey a clear interaction affordance and maintain consistency across experiences. The component does not support any other icons.



                                                                                                                                Usage

                                                                                                                                Use sliding buttons to let users take important actions. They should be used as the last step in a multi-step flow (like requesting or completing a trip) or to introduce friction to confirm a user’s intent and prevent button mashing (like calling 911).

                                                                                                                                Use cases

                                                                                                                                Prevent accidental action
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Sliding buttons can bring intentional friction to long flows with continuous primary action placement. The differentiation in interaction patterns can help prevent button mashing.

                                                                                                                                Confirm intent on costly/non-reversible actions
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Users are required to take deliberate and intentional steps to confirm their intent before taking a costly or non-reversible action like calling 911 or completing a payment.

                                                                                                                                Caution
                                                                                                                                If the action is not critical, a sliding button may be unnecessary and may add unnecessary complexity to the interface.


                                                                                                                                Mobile environments only

                                                                                                                                Using a swipe interaction as an action gesture feels natural in a mobile environment.

                                                                                                                                We discourage using sliding buttons in a desktop environment. Trying to complete the task with a mouse or trackpad feels unnatural and is not a widely spread pattern.


                                                                                                                                Behavior

                                                                                                                                Users can drag on the arrow affordance. Once the arrow reaches a threshold, the Sliding button's action will be triggered.

                                                                                                                                States

                                                                                                                                Preloading
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Placeholder component

                                                                                                                                Enabled
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text: contentPrimary

                                                                                                                                Icon: contentInversePrimary

                                                                                                                                Container: backgroundInversePrimary

                                                                                                                                Focus
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text: contentPrimary

                                                                                                                                Icon: contentInversePrimary

                                                                                                                                Container: backgroundInversePrimary

                                                                                                                                Outline: 3px borderAccent

                                                                                                                                On drag
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                While a sliding button is being dragged, the button text has a contentState﻿Disabled fill.

                                                                                                                                Loading
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Spinner replaces the content and arrow affordance is removed

                                                                                                                                Disabled
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text and icons: contentStateDisabled

                                                                                                                                Container: backgroundStateDisabled

                                                                                                                                Slide affordance

                                                                                                                                Auto-complete thresholds

                                                                                                                                Users can slide the button to complete an action upon passing a threshold. We currently provide two threshold levels to support different user types.

                                                                                                                                Demanding a high degree of interaction precision to complete an action proves difficult to users with physical and motor disabilities, as well as seniors. When choosing which threshold to use, think about who your users are and whether they’d find it difficult to interact with the component in the “Hard” slide mode.

                                                                                                                                Threshold

                                                                                                                                Value

                                                                                                                                Low (Easy)

                                                                                                                                Complete more than 20%

                                                                                                                                High (Hard)

                                                                                                                                Complete more than 80%

                                                                                                                                Low threshold (Easy)

                                                                                                                                High threshold (Hard)

                                                                                                                                Haptics

                                                                                                                                (iOS)

                                                                                                                                Failure
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                On failure, play a Failure haptic pattern (native to iOS) after restarting the state of the button.

                                                                                                                                On touch down
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                On touch down, play a single haptic nudge to confirm the affordance has been engaged.

                                                                                                                                Success
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                On success, play a Success haptic pattern (native to iOS) to reinforce the request has been successfully submitted.

                                                                                                                                Breakpoints

                                                                                                                                Sliding buttons should follow the same Button breakpoints rules defined in our buttons documentation.

                                                                                                                                Overrides

                                                                                                                                Color

                                                                                                                                Background color
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Background color customizations of the sliding button are supported but stick to using primary, high-contrast colors like: InverseBackgroundPrimary, backgroundAccent, backgroundNegative, and backgroundPositive.

                                                                                                                                Ensure your text and icon colors work on top of your chosen background. Ensure your custom background color is tokenized so it flips to dark mode.

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Distinguish the swipe affordance from the surrounding UI by using a primary, high-contrast background.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Do not inverse the button styles or use secondary styling on the swipe affordance. For more guidance on color, check out the Colors section of this documentation.

                                                                                                                                Size

                                                                                                                                Avoid resizing elements inside the button, like the icon or sliding button affordance. Try going up or down in size for the entire button instead.

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Keep the sliding button height and the base button height the same.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Do not enlarge or shrink either part of the sliding button.



                                                                                                                                Examples

                                                                                                                                Rides confirmation page
                                                                                                                                Emergency assistance
                                                                                                                                Retriever
                                                                                                                                Driver CoreEx
